<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="893" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d893">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Curry</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-26"><hi rend="italic">June 26,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 3.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch of May 31, 1902, reporting your reception as ambassador
                            extraordinary of the United States on a special mission to attend the
                            ceremonies on the occasion of the coming of age of Alphonso XIII.</p>
                        <p>The Department is gratified to learn of the appreciative reception
                            accorded to you, as a forecast of the good will which this Government
                            trusts will ever prevail between the United States and Spain.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>